    %form{:action => "/wwwjdic.cgi?19A", :method => "POST"}
      %h3 Customization Page
      You are able to customize various aspects of
      = succeed "'s" do
        %b WWWJDIC
      display
      and operation.
      Select from the options below, and press the "Customize" button at the bottom of the
      page.
      (Note: the older "customized URL" method is being withdrawn.)
      %p
      %ul
        %li
          Maximum dictionary entries per search results page:
          %input{:name => "maxlines", :size => "3", :type => "text", :value => "10"}/
          (Upper limit is 100)
          %br/
        %li
          Maximum detail lines per kanji database display:
          %input{:name => "maxklines", :size => "3", :type => "text", :value => "5"}/
          (Upper limit is 50)
          %br/
          %font{:size => "-1"}
            (When you look up the kanji database and there are several kanji
            which meet the search criteria, this parameter is used to choose whether details
            are displayed, or whether a simple list of kanji is displayed for you to choose
            from.)
          %br/
        %li
          Input/Output code:
          %select{:name => "icode"}
            %option{:selected => "", :value => "1"}
              EUC-JP
            %option{:value => "2"}
              Shift-JIS
            %option{:value => "3"}
              UTF-8
          %br/
          %font{:size => "-1"} (If you don't know what these are, don't touch it.)
          %br/
        %li
          Background colour:
          %select{:name => "bgcolour"}
            %option{:selected => "", :value => "ivory"}
              ivory
            %option{:value => "aqua"}
              aqua
            %option{:value => "black"}
              black
            %option{:value => "blue"}
              blue
            %option{:value => "fuchsia"}
              fuchsia
            %option{:value => "gray"}
              gray
            %option{:value => "green"}
              green
            %option{:value => "lime"}
              lime
            %option{:value => "maroon"}
              maroon
            %option{:value => "navy"}
              navy
            %option{:value => "olive"}
              olive
            %option{:value => "purple"}
              purple
            %option{:value => "red"}
              red
            %option{:value => "silver"}
              silver
            %option{:value => "teal"}
              teal
            %option{:value => "yellow"}
              yellow
            %option{:value => "white"}
              white
          or specify your own
          = succeed "(*)" do
            %input{:name => "bgcolourx", :size => "20", :type => "text", :value => ""}/
          %br/
        %li
          Text colour:
          %select{:name => "txtcolour"}
            %option{:value => "aqua"}
              aqua
            %option{:selected => "", :value => "black"}
              black
            %option{:value => "blue"}
              blue
            %option{:value => "fuchsia"}
              fuchsia
            %option{:value => "gray"}
              gray
            %option{:value => "green"}
              green
            %option{:value => "lime"}
              lime
            %option{:value => "maroon"}
              maroon
            %option{:value => "navy"}
              navy
            %option{:value => "olive"}
              olive
            %option{:value => "purple"}
              purple
            %option{:value => "red"}
              red
            %option{:value => "silver"}
              silver
            %option{:value => "teal"}
              teal
            %option{:value => "yellow"}
              yellow
            %option{:value => "white"}
              white
          or specify your own
          = succeed "(*)" do
            %input{:name => "txtcolourx", :size => "20", :type => "text", :value => ""}/
          %br/
          (*):
          %ol{:type => "a"}
            %li
              if you are keying your own colours, make
              %b sure
              your browser
              supports them.)
            %li
              if you have selected a different colour previously, you will need
              to clear the text field if you wish to change it.
        %li
          Interface language:
          %select{:name => "langcode"}
            %option{:selected => "", :value => "0"}
              English
            %option{:value => "1"}
              Japanese
          %font{:color => "red"} (Japanese version is under construction!)
          %br/
        %li
          the information and options in the page header and the main
          dictionary results pages.
          %p
            The following are normally
            %b enabled
            by default. You can selectively remove
            them here.
          %table{:border => ""}
            %tr
              %td
                %b O P T I O N
              %td
                %b Enable
              %td
                %b Disable
            %tr
              %td
                Menu Bar at the top of the page
                %em (removal NOT recommended)
              %td
                %input{:checked => "", :name => "opt_menubar", :type => "radio", :value => "1"}/
              %td
                %input{:name => "opt_menubar", :type => "radio", :value => "0"}/
            %tr
              %td
                The explanation of the options ([G]oogle, etc.)
              %td
                %input{:checked => "", :name => "opt_optexpl", :type => "radio", :value => "1"}/
              %td
                %input{:name => "opt_optexpl", :type => "radio", :value => "0"}/
            %tr
              %td
